# UI Design Conventions

## Fluid Responsive Layouts

Content should **fill available screen space** and adapt to all screen sizes. Never use fixed max-widths that make content look sparse on larger monitors.

```scss
// ❌ BAD - Fixed max-width leaves empty space on large screens
.page {
  max-width: 1000px;
}

// ✅ GOOD - Fluid width fills available space
.page {
  width: 100%;
}
```

## Responsive Approach

- Use `width: 100%` for containers and content areas
- Tables should stretch to fill available width
- Use responsive padding that scales with viewport (smaller on mobile, larger on desktop)
- Split-view panels can have fixed widths for sidebars, but main content should be fluid

```scss
// ✅ GOOD - Responsive padding
.content {
  padding: $space-4;  // 16px mobile

  @include md {
    padding: $space-5;  // 20px tablet
  }

  @include lg {
    padding: $space-6;  // 24px desktop
  }
}
```

## Component Sizing

- Inputs/buttons: Use consistent heights (32-34px for compact UI)
- Search inputs: Full width on mobile, max-width on larger screens
- Tables: Always `width: 100%`, let columns distribute naturally
